<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Barry tells FRONTLINE that it is unclear whether the Special Forces soldiers knew about this incident. However he says, &quot;It is clear from the beginning of this year the Defense Department and officials elsewhere in the administration knew, first of all, that there were allegations of mass slaughter of the prisoners from Kunduz; and secondly that there was a mass grave outside the prison.&quot; He remarked, &quot;I'm reminded of the old proverb, there is none so blind as them who will not see.&quot;<br>
